meta.commit_message: ⚡ Tidy superconductors part 2 \(#3659\) CITATION.cff CMakeLists.txt CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md CONTRIBUTING.md LICENSE.txt README.md cmake documentation examples mkdocs.yml process process-tracking-data process.egg-info requirements.txt requirements_dev.txt ruff.toml scripts setup.py source tests tracking valgrind-python.supp :memo: Update documentation and refactor ITER Nb3Sn critical surface implementation for clarity and consistency CITATION.cff CMakeLists.txt CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md CONTRIBUTING.md LICENSE.txt README.md cmake documentation examples mkdocs.yml process process-tracking-data process.egg-info requirements.txt requirements_dev.txt ruff.toml scripts setup.py source tests tracking valgrind-python.supp Enhance documentation and add Bi-2212 critical surface plotting - Updated the superconductors documentation to include detailed information on Bi-2212\, including its critical current density and temperature margin calculations. - Added an interactive version of the critical surface graph for Bi-2212. - Created a new Python script for plotting the critical current density surface of Bi-2212 at zero strain\, utilizing both Matplotlib and Plotly for visualization. - Refactored the bi2212 function in the superconductors module to improve parameterization and documentation clarity. CITATION.cff CMakeLists.txt CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md CONTRIBUTING.md LICENSE.txt README.md cmake documentation examples mkdocs.yml process process-tracking-data process.egg-info requirements.txt requirements_dev.txt ruff.toml scripts setup.py source tests tracking valgrind-python.supp Add old empirical NbTi critical surface model and associated documentation - Introduced a new image file \`old_NbTi_zero_strain.png\` depicting the critical current density surface for old NbTi superconductors. - Updated \`superconductors.md\` to include a section on the old empirical Lubell scaling for NbTi\, detailing critical parameters and equations. - Added a new Python script \`old_empirical_nbti_critical_surface.py\` for plotting the critical current density surface using the old empirical model. - Enhanced the \`jcrit_nbti\` function in \`superconductors.py\` to include detailed docstring references and notes about the antiquated scaling law used for NbTi. CITATION.cff CMakeLists.txt CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md CONTRIBUTING.md LICENSE.txt README.md cmake documentation examples mkdocs.yml process process-tracking-data process.egg-info requirements.txt requirements_dev.txt ruff.toml scripts setup.py source tests tracking valgrind-python.supp Add Durham NbTi model for critical current density - Introduced a new image file \`Durham_NbTi_zero_strain.png\` to visualize the critical current density surface. - Updated \`superconductors.md\` to include a detailed description of the Durham model\, its derivation\, and parameters. - Created a new Python script \`durham_nbti_critical_surface.py\` for plotting the critical current density surface using the Durham model. - Enhanced the \`gl_nbti\` function in \`superconductors.py\` to calculate critical current density\, critical field\, and critical temperature based on the Ginzburg-Landau theory\, with updated parameter handling and documentation.
